topic.title: Extended Partition Port Count Support

body.p: PCIe topologies are limited to a total of 32 devices per bus under the current PCIe Base Specification Bus/Device/Function allocation with a Device ID represented as a 5 bit field. Since each DSP consumes a device ID, this creates a limit on the number of DSPs that can be supported in a conventional switch. Switchtec can optionally support more than 32 DSPs in each partition by using the 3-bit Function field.

Switchtec automatically enables this multi-function device assignment when the number of DSPs in a partition is more than 32. If a partition's port map contains 32 or fewer DSPs, conventional DSP device assignment will be used. If a partition's port map contains more than 32 DSPs, multi-function DSP device assignment will be used. The host bios/os enumerates a non-multi function DSP.

section.title: Conventional DSP Device Assignment
section.p: In cases where a partition contains 32 or fewer DSPs, device numbers are allocated using standard PCIe enumeration rules. For example, if 32 DSPs are configured on bus 2 their B/D/F identifiers are as show in Table 1.

section.title: Multi-Function DSP Device Assignment
section.p: In cases where a partition contains more than 32 DSPs, device and function numbers are allocated to each DSP. The device numbers will not be incremented until the function field is fully allocated as illustrated in Table 2.
